==Description==

The [[Image:Part_Common.svg|24px]] '''Part Common''' tool extracts the common part (intersection) between selected Part objects. This operation is fully parametric and the components can be modified and the result recomputed.

This tool is an automated form of the [[Image:Part_Boolean.svg|16px|link=Part_Boolean]] [[Part_Boolean|Boolean operation]].

[[Image:Common_example.PNG|480px]]

== Usage ==

# Select two shapes
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Part_Common.svg|16px]] [[Part_Common|Intersection]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Part → Boolean → [[Image:Part_Common.svg|16px]] Intersection}} option from the menu.

== Supported inputs ==

Input objects must be [[OpenCASCADE|OpenCASCADE]] shapes. Examples: stuff made with Part, PartDesign, Sketcher workbenches. Not meshes (unless those were converted to shapes) - for meshes, there are specific Boolean tools in MeshDesign workbench.


